Machakos county should solve the deteriorating sanitation in Athi River and Mlolongo towns, Athi River deputy county commissioner Geoffrey Omoding (pictured) has said. He said the filthy situationmay lead to dieseas outbreak. There is public outcry on the pathetic condition of sanitation in the subcounty. Residents are finding it hard to live with solid waste and raw sewerage flowing in the open, he said.